title: Dakota pipeline protesters leave site after year-long occupation
text:
A year-long protest against an oil pipeline in North Dakota appears to be nearing its end, as a government deadline for demonstrators to leave the area passes.
Some demonstrators who ignored requests to depart were arrested, and makeshift wooden structures were set ablaze.
Read more Dakota pipeline protesters leave site after year-long occupation
